                <div class="block_content">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-sm-12">
                            <h1 class="page-title">Government approved “nursing benefits” for the self-employed II</h1>
                        </div>

                    </div>
                                        <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-sm-12">
                            <div class="row">
                                
                                <div class="col-sm-9">
                                    <div class="row">
                                        <div class="col-xs-3">Published:</div>
                                        <div class="col-xs-9"><span style="color: #c21f15;">16.10.2020</span></div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row">
                                        <div class="col-xs-3" style="width: 20% !important;">Author:</div>
                                        <div class="col-xs-9"><span style="color: #000;">Communication department</span></div>
                                    </div>
                                    <br />
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div style="font-style:italic;"><p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">CZK 400 per day is a &ldquo;nursing benefit&rdquo; to be obtained by self-employed persons affected by the coronavirus pandemic. The government has approved a proposal by the Ministry of Industry and Trade to support entrepreneurs who, due to the closure of a school or other facility, cannot fully conduct business and care for a child under 10 years of age or a disabled loved one.</p>
</div>
                            <br />
                            <p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm"><em>&ldquo;I am glad that the government has approved my proposal to renew the &ldquo;Nursing benefits&rdquo; program for the self-employed, no attachment will be attached to the application, only a solemn declaration will suffice&rdquo;</em> says <strong>Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Industry and Trade Karel Havlíček.</strong></p>

<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">The support is intended for people who cannot perform a self-employed main activity due to the caring for a child under 10 years of age or a disabled person. If they meet the set conditions, they can receive assistance in the amount of CZK 400 per calendar day. The &ldquo;nursing benefits&rdquo; will be applied for via an intelligent online form, which will be available, as well as all detailed information, on the MIT website.</p>

<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm"><em>&ldquo;Those who receive a disability or old-age pension, have another job, receive parental allowance or maternity allowance are not entitled to support. We appeal to all entrepreneurs to send their applications only electronically so as to receive their money much earlier&rdquo;</em> says <strong>Pavel Vinkler, Director of the Department of the Business Environment and Business Entrepreneurship of the Ministry of Industry and Trade.</strong></p>

<p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm">The program is designed as a framework and will be announced through calls. In the first stage, CZK 200 million is allocated from the budget of the Ministry of Industry and Trade.</p>

                            <br />

                                    </div>
                    </div>
                            

                </div>
